### 🟡 Medium — Poor Naming (`_Works` pattern)

**Location:** All 10 test methods

Every test is named `Method_Works` which communicates no scenario or expected outcome. When a test fails in CI, `UpdatePrice_Works FAILED` tells you nothing. Good names encode the precondition and expected result.

**Pattern:** `Method_Scenario_ExpectedOutcome`

| Current | Suggested |
|---------|-----------|
| `AddProduct_Works` | `AddProduct_NewSku_ProductIsRetrievable` |
| `GetProduct_Works` | `GetProduct_ExistingSku_ReturnsCorrectProduct` |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | `UpdatePrice_ExistingProduct_PriceIsUpdated` |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | `RemoveProduct_ExistingSku_ProductNoLongerFound` |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | `GetProductCount_AfterAddingTwo_ReturnsTwo` |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | `ImportFromCsv_ValidLine_ProductIsPersisted` |

